722301f-c.text:
Park Avenue, south from East 6lst Street, showing prominently buildings on the east side of same,viewed south westward across tho cleared west frontage thnt oxtends to 60th Street. The low structures appearing on the right are at 59th S.reet, the white building being the Mineola Garage and the other the old Arion Hall (erected 1887). Upon the cleared land in the foreground was erected Christ Church; the balance being utilised by the Park Ave. Tennis Clubs. In 1940 the latter will be replaced by a
19 story apartment house.
The photographer's vantage pofnt is Enst 61st St.
slightly west of the Avenue.
Viows 1,2 December 21, 1930
View 3 May 13, 1930
P. L. Sperr
